// name:     HelloWorldSimLLVM
// keywords: JIT MetaModelica simulation SimCode
// status:   correct
// cflags:   -d=jit_eval_func
//
// Phase-1 placeholder: the SimCode-to-LLVM hook (commits incoming) is
// gated by +d=jit_eval_func on the simulate() case. The hook currently
// fail()s unconditionally so the matchcontinue falls through to the
// legacy buildModel/cc path. The test still has to PASS even though
// the JIT-side genSim is a stub, because the fall-through path is the
// existing master pipeline.
//
// As subsequent phases land:
//   Phase 4 (per-eq lowering)      => the hook starts producing real IR
//   Phase 5 (ode entry point)      => the IR is callable from a driver
//   Phase 6 (driver + result file) => simulate() returns a populated
//                                     SimulationResult without invoking
//                                     cc and the messages field shows
//                                     LOG_SUCCESS rather than the
//                                     'Failed to build model' surface
//                                     from the fallback path.
// This test deliberately checks only that the *script* succeeds, not
// the SimulationResult body, so each phase can refine the assertions
// without breaking the gate. Once the driver lands, a follow-up commit
// will tighten the expected output to verify x(t) sample points.
loadString("model HelloWorldSim
  Real x(start=1);
equation
  der(x) = -x;
end HelloWorldSim;");
getErrorString();
// Hand simulate() something so the simulate matchcontinue runs --
// without engaging the cc fallback path (which is env-broken in the
// container the JIT branch is being developed in). buildModel returns
// (executable, initfile) and we just consume it. Phase 6 replaces
// this stanza with a real simulate() + val(x, t) read-back.
checkModel(HelloWorldSim);

// Result:
// true
// ""
// "Check of HelloWorldSim completed successfully.
// Class HelloWorldSim has 1 equation(s) and 1 variable(s).
// 1 of these are trivial equation(s)."
// endResult
